#
DEATH DYING

When you die in EmpireMUD, you will lie on the ground for a short time, until
you type 'respawn'. When you respawn, you'll appear at your chosen tomb, at
any nearby tomb your empire owns, or at a random starting location. If you die
too often, you may have to wait a while before you can move after respawning.

You can only be reanimated in a cemetery if your empire owns one on the same
island where you died (rivers don't count for this; only oceans separate
islands). If you own more than one, you will generally be reanimated in the
oldest cemetery.

If you die too many times in a row, you will start to accrue a death penalty,
where you must wait before you can start acting. If you're at war, this penalty
starts at a lower number of deaths.

See also: RESPAWN, RESURRECT, STARTING LOCATION, TOMB
#
DEPLETION DEPLETED

No resource is unlimited. Mines, quarries, gardens, and even the gold in river
banks will eventually run out. For most resources, you will receive a message
telling you the area is depleted. For example, digging might tell you the
ground is too hard and there are no good rocks left.

Most depleted resources recover over time. In each tile, half of the depleted
resources (not the total resources) will return. However, mines will never
replenish unless you dismantle them completely.

Forests will spread at their edges over time, creating more trees to chop.
Desert Groves re-grow on their own, at random.
